Here's a self-contained HTML file that handles all your requirements:

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0"/>
  <title>CSV Parser</title>
  <style>
    /* ── Reset & Base ── */
    *, *::before, *::after { box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0; padding: 0; }

    body {
      font-family: 'Segoe UI', Tahoma, Geneva, Verdana, sans-serif;
      background: #f0f2f5;
      color: #2c3e50;
      min-height: 100vh;
      padding: 2rem;
    }

    /* ── Page Header ── */
    h1 {
      text-align: center;
      font-size: 1.8rem;
      margin-bottom: 0.3rem;
      color: #1a252f;
      letter-spacing: 0.5px;
    }

    .subtitle {
      text-align: center;
      font-size: 0.9rem;
      color: #7f8c8d;
      margin-bottom: 2rem;
    }

    /* ── Card Container ── */
    .card {
      background: #ffffff;
      border-radius: 10px;
      box-shadow: 0 4px 16px rgba(0,0,0,0.10);
      padding: 1.8rem 2rem;
      max-width: 960px;
      margin: 0 auto 2rem auto;
    }

    /* ── Textarea ── */
    label[for="csvInput"] {
      display: block;
      font-weight: 600;
      margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
      font-size: 0.95rem;
    }

    #csvInput {
      width: 100%;
      height: 180px;
      padding: 0.75rem 1rem;
      border: 2px solid #dce1e7;
      border-radius: 7px;
      font-family: 'Courier New', Courier, monospace;
      font-size: 0.88rem;
      color: #2c3e50;
      background: #f9fafb;
      resize: vertical;
      transition: border-color 0.2s;
      outline: none;
    }

    #csvInput:focus {
      border-color: #3498db;
      background: #fff;
    }

    /* ── Controls Row ── */
    .controls {
      display: flex;
      align-items: center;
      gap: 1rem;
      margin-top: 1rem;
      flex-wrap: wrap;
    }

    /* ── Parse Button ── */
    #parseBtn {
      padding: 0.6rem 1.8rem;
      background: #3498db;
      color: #fff;
      border: none;
      border-radius: 7px;
      font-size: 0.95rem;
      font-weight: 600;
      cursor: pointer;
      transition: background 0.2s, transform 0.1s;
    }

    #parseBtn:hover  { background: #2980b9; }
    #parseBtn:active { transform: scale(0.97); }

    /* ── Clear Button ── */
    #clearBtn {
      padding: 0.6rem 1.4rem;
      background: transparent;
      color: #e74c3c;
      border: 2px solid #e74c3c;
      border-radius: 7px;
      font-size: 0.95rem;
      font-weight: 600;
      cursor: pointer;
      transition: background 0.2s, color 0.2s;
    }

    #clearBtn:hover {
      background: #e74c3c;
      color: #fff;
    }

    /* ── Header-row toggle ── */
    .toggle-label {
      display: flex;
      align-items: center;
      gap: 0.4rem;
      font-size: 0.88rem;
      cursor: pointer;
      user-select: none;
    }

    .toggle-label input { cursor: pointer; accent-color: #3498db; }

    /* ── Status / Error Message ── */
    #statusMsg {
      margin-top: 0.8rem;
      font-size: 0.88rem;
      min-height: 1.2em;
    }

    #statusMsg.error   { color: #e74c3c; }
    #statusMsg.success { color: #27ae60; }

    /* ── Table Wrapper ── */
    #tableWrapper {
      max-width: 960px;
      margin: 0 auto;
      overflow-x: auto;
      border-radius: 10px;
      box-shadow: 0 4px 16px rgba(0,0,0,0.09);
      display: none;          /* hidden until data is parsed */
    }

    /* ── Table ── */
    table {
      width: 100%;
      border-collapse: collapse;
      font-size: 0.88rem;
      background: #fff;
    }

    /* Header row */
    thead tr th {
      background: #2c3e50;
      color: #ecf0f1;
      padding: 0.75rem 1rem;
      text-align: left;
      font-weight: 600;
      border: 1px solid #1a252f;
      white-space: nowrap;
      position: sticky;
      top: 0;
      z-index: 1;
    }

    /* Body rows */
    tbody tr td {
      padding: 0.6rem 1rem;
      border: 1px solid #dce1e7;
      vertical-align: top;
      word-break: break-word;
    }

    /* Alternating row colours */
    tbody tr:nth-child(odd)  td { background: #ffffff; }
    tbody tr:nth-child(even) td { background: #eaf3fb; }

    /* Hover highlight */
    tbody tr:hover td { background: #d6eaf8; }

    /* Empty-cell indicator */
    td.empty-cell {
      color: #bdc3c7;
      font-style: italic;
      font-size: 0.82rem;
    }

    /* Row-number column */
    td.row-num, th.row-num {
      color: #95a5a6;
      font-size: 0.78rem;
      text-align: right;
      white-space: nowrap;
      width: 1%;
      padding-right: 0.8rem;
    }

    th.row-num { background: #1a252f; }

    /* ── Footer stats ── */
    #tableStats {
      text-align: right;
      font-size: 0.8rem;
      color: #95a5a6;
      padding: 0.5rem 1rem;
      background: #f9fafb;
      border-top: 1px solid #dce1e7;
    }

    /* ── Responsive tweak ── */
    @media (max-width: 600px) {
      body { padding: 1rem; }
      .card { padding: 1.2rem; }
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>

  <h1>📊 CSV Parser</h1>
  <p class="subtitle">Paste your CSV data below and click <strong>Parse CSV</strong></p>

  <!-- Input card -->
  <div class="card">
    <label for="csvInput">CSV Data</label>
    <textarea
      id="csvInput"
      spellcheck="false"
      placeholder='Paste CSV here, e.g.:
Name,Age,City
"Smith, John",30,"New York"
"O&apos;Brien ""Tim""",25,London'
    ></textarea>

    <div class="controls">
      <button id="parseBtn">▶ Parse CSV</button>
      <button id="clearBtn">✕ Clear</button>
      <label class="toggle-label">
        <input type="checkbox" id="headerToggle" checked />
        First row is header
      </label>
    </div>

    <div id="statusMsg"></div>
  </div>

  <!-- Output table -->
  <div id="tableWrapper">
    <table id="outputTable">
      <thead id="outputHead"></thead>
      <tbody id="outputBody"></tbody>
    </table>
    <div id="tableStats"></div>
  </div>

  <script>
    /* ─────────────────────────────────────────────
       RFC 4180-compliant CSV parser
       Handles:
         • Quoted fields (may contain commas)
         • Escaped quotes inside quoted fields ("")
         • Bare (unquoted) fields
         • \r\n, \n, \r line endings
         • Varying column counts per row
    ───────────────────────────────────────────── */
    function parseCSV(text) {
      const rows   = [];
      let   row    = [];
      let   field  = '';
      let   inQuote = false;
      let   i      = 0;
      const len    = text.length;

      while (i < len) {
        const ch   = text[i];
        const next = text[i + 1];

        if (inQuote) {
          if (ch === '"') {
            if (next === '"') {
              // Escaped quote: "" → "
              field += '"';
              i += 2;
            } else {
              // Closing quote
              inQuote = false;
              i++;
            }
          } else {
            field += ch;
            i++;
          }
        } else {
          if (ch === '"') {
            // Opening quote
            inQuote = true;
            i++;
          } else if (ch === ',') {
            // Field separator
            row.push(field);
            field = '';
            i++;
          } else if (ch === '\r' && next === '\n') {
            // Windows line ending
            row.push(field);
            rows.push(row);
            row   = [];
            field = '';
            i += 2;
          } else if (ch === '\n' || ch === '\r') {
            // Unix / old-Mac line ending
            row.push(field);
            rows.push(row);
            row   = [];
            field = '';
            i++;
          } else {
            field += ch;
            i++;
          }
        }
      }

      // Push the last field / row (no trailing newline)
      if (field !== '' || row.length > 0) {
        row.push(field);
        rows.push(row);
      }

      // Drop a single completely-empty trailing row
      if (rows.length > 0) {
        const last = rows[rows.length - 1];
        if (last.length === 1 && last[0] === '') rows.pop();
      }

      return rows;
    }

    /* ─────────────────────────────────────────────
       Build the HTML table from parsed rows
    ───────────────────────────────────────────── */
    function buildTable(rows, firstRowIsHeader) {
      const thead      = document.getElementById('outputHead');
      const tbody      = document.getElementById('outputBody');
      const tableStats = document.getElementById('tableStats');

      thead.innerHTML = '';
      tbody.innerHTML = '';

      if (rows.length === 0) return;

      // Find the maximum column count across all rows
      const maxCols = rows.reduce((m, r) => Math.max(m, r.length), 0);

      /* Helper: create a cell with optional empty-cell styling */
      function makeCell(tag, text, extraClass) {
        const el = document.createElement(tag);
        if (text === '') {
          el.textContent = '(empty)';
          el.classList.add('empty-cell');
        } else {
          el.textContent = text;
        }
        if (extraClass) el.classList.add(extraClass);
        return el;
      }

      /* ── Header row ── */
      const headerTr = document.createElement('tr');

      // Row-number stub
      const rnTh = document.createElement('th');
      rnTh.classList.add('row-num');
      rnTh.textContent = '#';
      headerTr.appendChild(rnTh);

      const headerData = firstRowIsHeader ? rows[0] : null;

      for (let c = 0; c < maxCols; c++) {
        const label = headerData
          ? (headerData[c] !== undefined ? headerData[c] : '')
          : `Column ${c + 1}`;
        const th = document.createElement('th');
        th.textContent = label || `Column ${c + 1}`;
        headerTr.appendChild(th);
      }
      thead.appendChild(headerTr);

      /* ── Body rows ── */
      const dataRows = firstRowIsHeader ? rows.slice(1) : rows;

      dataRows.forEach((row, idx) => {
        const tr = document.createElement('tr');

        // Row number
        const rnTd = document.createElement('td');
        rnTd.classList.add('row-num');
        rnTd.textContent = idx + 1;
        tr.appendChild(rnTd);

        for (let c = 0; c < maxCols; c++) {
          const val = row[c] !== undefined ? row[c] : '';
          tr.appendChild(makeCell('td', val));
        }
        tbody.appendChild(tr);
      });

      /* ── Stats footer ── */
      const dataCount = dataRows.length;
      const colWord   = maxCols === 1 ? 'column' : 'columns';
      const rowWord   = dataCount === 1 ? 'row' : 'rows';
      tableStats.textContent =
        `${dataCount} data ${rowWord} · ${maxCols} ${colWord}` +
        (firstRowIsHeader ? ' · first row used as header' : '');
    }

    /* ─────────────────────────────────────────────
       UI wiring
    ───────────────────────────────────────────── */
    const csvInput     = document.getElementById('csvInput');
    const parseBtn     = document.getElementById('parseBtn');
    const clearBtn     = document.getElementById('clearBtn');
    const headerToggle = document.getElementById('headerToggle');
    const statusMsg    = document.getElementById('statusMsg');
    const tableWrapper = document.getElementById('tableWrapper');

    function setStatus(msg, type) {
      statusMsg.textContent = msg;
      statusMsg.className   = type; // 'error' | 'success' | ''
    }

    function runParse() {
      const raw = csvInput.value;

      if (!raw.trim()) {
        setStatus('⚠ Please paste some CSV data first.', 'error');
        tableWrapper.style.display = 'none';
        return;
      }

      try {
        const rows = parseCSV(raw);

        if (rows.length === 0) {
          setStatus('⚠ No data found after parsing.', 'error');
          tableWrapper.style.display = 'none';
          return;
        }

        const useHeader = headerToggle.checked;

        // Warn if header-mode is on but there's only one row
        if (useHeader && rows.length === 1) {
          setStatus(
            '⚠ Only one row found — it will be used as the header with no data rows.',
            'error'
          );
        } else {
          const dataRows = useHeader ? rows.length - 1 : rows.length;
          setStatus(
            `✔ Parsed successfully — ${dataRows} data row${dataRows !== 1 ? 's' : ''} found.`,
            'success'
          );
        }

        buildTable(rows, useHeader);
        tableWrapper.style.display = 'block';

      } catch (err) {
        setStatus(`✖ Parse error: ${err.message}`, 'error');
        tableWrapper.style.display = 'none';
      }
    }

    parseBtn.addEventListener('click', runParse);

    clearBtn.addEventListener('click', () => {
      csvInput.value             = '';
      statusMsg.textContent      = '';
      statusMsg.className        = '';
      tableWrapper.style.display = 'none';
      csvInput.focus();
    });

    // Allow Ctrl+Enter to trigger parse
    csvInput.addEventListener('keydown', (e) => {
      if ((e.ctrlKey || e.metaKey) && e.key === 'Enter') runParse();
    });

    // Re-parse automatically when the header toggle changes
    headerToggle.addEventListener('change', () => {
      if (tableWrapper.style.display === 'block') runParse();
    });
  </script>
</body>
</html>
```

---

### What's included and why

| Feature | Detail |
|---|---|
| **RFC 4180 parser** | Character-by-character state machine — correctly handles `""` escaped quotes, quoted fields with commas, and all three line endings (`\r\n`, `\n`, `\r`) |
| **Varying column counts** | Finds the maximum column count across all rows and pads shorter rows with empty cells |
| **Styled table** | Dark sticky header, alternating blue-tinted / white rows, hover highlight, clear 1 px borders |
| **Row numbers** | A muted `#` column lets you track position at a glance |
| **Empty-cell indicator** | Empty fields show `(empty)` in light grey italic so they're never invisible |
| **Header toggle** | Checkbox to treat the first row as a header or as data — re-parses live |
| **Status messages** | Green success / red error feedback beneath the controls |
| **Stats footer** | Shows row count, column count, and header mode below the table |
| **Keyboard shortcut** | `Ctrl+Enter` (or `Cmd+Enter`) triggers parsing |
| **Responsive** | Horizontally scrollable table wrapper; tightened padding on small screens |

