### What makes the parsing actually correct

| Scenario | How it's handled |
|---|---|
| `"Smith, John"` — comma inside quotes | Parser enters quoted-field mode on `"`, accumulates chars freely until the **closing** `"` — comma is never treated as a delimiter |
| `""escaped""` — doubled quotes | When inside a quoted field and `text[i] === '"'`, the parser peeks at `text[i+1]`; if it's also `"` it emits one literal `"` and advances **two** positions |
| Multi-line fields | Newlines inside a quoted field are accumulated as regular characters, not treated as row terminators |
| Mixed quoted/unquoted on same row | Each field is evaluated independently at the start of each field position |
| Trailing empty rows | Stripped before rendering so you don't get a ghost final row |

